INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (339,1,'2025-10-01 00:02:19','2025-10-01 00:02:19','Steinen kommer fra sokkelen til en statue av Fridtjof Nansen. Skulpturen ble flyttet dit i 1964 fra Frammuseet på Bygdøy.\nFridtjof Nansen (1861-1930) er en av Norges mest allsidige og internasjonalt berømte personer gjennom tidene. Han var en banebrytende naturforsker, polarekspedisjonsleder, forfatter,kunstner, diplomat og filantrop. Han ble tildelt Nobels fredspris i 1922.\nSkimuseet er verdens eldste og Norges største samling av ski og annet vinterutstyr. Det eies av Foreningen til Ski-Idrettens Fremme. Museet ble åpnet i 1923 på Frognerseteren i Oslo, og flyttet i 1951 til Holmenkollbakken med lokaler inne i selve hoppet. Siden 1983 har det holdt til i nye lokaler i fjellet ved siden av, tegnet av arkitekt Arnstein Friling og utvidet i perioden 1997–1999.\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Fridtjof_Nansen\">Fridtjof Nansen – polarfarer, humanist, diplomat</a>\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Skimuseet\">Skimuseet – Store norske leksikon</a>','Sokkel for Fridtjof Nansen statue, Holmenkollen, Oslo','','publish','closed','closed','','holmenkollen','','','2025-10-01 00:02:19','2025-10-01 00:02:19','',0,'https://example.com/?post_type=entry&amp;p=339',70,'entry','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (340,1,'2025-10-01 00:02:20','2025-10-01 00:02:20','The stone comes from the pedestal of a statue of Fridtjof Nansen. The sculpture was moved there in 1964 from Frammuseet on Bygdøy.\nFridtjof Nansen (1861-1930) is one of Norway\'s most versatile and internationally famous people of all time. He was a pioneering naturalist, polar expedition leader, author, artist, diplomat and philanthropist. He was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize in 1922.\nThe Ski Museum is the world\'s oldest and has Norway\'s largest collection of skis and other winter equipment. It is owned by the Association for the Promotion of Skiing. The museum was opened in 1923 at Frognerseteren inOslo andmoved to Holmenkollbakken in 1951 with premises inside the ski jump itself. Since 1983, it has been located in new premises in the mountain next door, designed by architect Arnstein Friling and expanded in the period 1997–1999.\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Fridtjof_Nansen\">Fridtjof Nansen – polar explorer, humanist, diplomat</a>\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Skimuseet\">Skiing museum – Store norske leksikon</a>','Plinth for Fridtjof Nansen statue, Holmenkollen, Oslo','','publish','closed','closed','','holmenkollen-en','','','2025-10-01 00:02:20','2025-10-01 00:02:20','',0,'https://example.com/?post_type=entry&amp;p=340',70,'entry','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (341,1,'2025-10-01 00:02:21','2025-10-01 00:02:21','Steinen kommer fra sokkelen til statuen av skøyteløperen Oscar Mathisen (1888-1954). Skulpturen er utført i 1958 av Arne Durban (1912-1993), og står utenfor Frogner stadion.\n<a href=\"https://okk.kunstsamlingen.no/search/1944/objects;jsessionid=D5E3C7F9C5394844FD3AC44E15780FB3\">Ukjent forfatter2026-01-09T00:27:00Hyper link was wrong, tried to replace, doesn’t seem to work.Oscar Mathisen (1888-1954</a> – Samlingen – Oslo kommunes kunstsamling)\nHyper link was wrong, tried to replace, doesn’t seem to work.\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Frogner_stadion\">Frogner stadion – Store norske leksikon (snl.no</a>)','Sokkel til bronseskulptur av Oscar Mathisen, Frogner stadion','','publish','closed','closed','','frogner_stadion','','','2025-10-01 00:02:21','2025-10-01 00:02:21','',0,'https://example.com/?post_type=entry&amp;p=341',71,'entry','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (342,1,'2025-10-01 00:02:22','2025-10-01 00:02:22','The stone comes from the pedestal of the statue of the skater Oscar Mathisen (1888-1954). The sculpture was made in 1958 by Arne Durban (1912-1993) and stands outside Frogner Stadium.\n<a href=\"https://okk.kunstsamlingen.no/search/1944/objects;jsessionid=D5E3C7F9C5394844FD3AC44E15780FB3\">Oscar Mathisen (1888-1954</a> – The collection – Oslo municipalitys art collection)\n<a href=\"https://snl.no/Frogner_stadion\">Frogner stadium – Store norske leksikon (snl.no</a>)','Plinth for bronze sculpture by Oscar Mathisen, Frogner stadium','','publish','closed','closed','','frogner_stadion-en','','','2025-10-01 00:02:22','2025-10-01 00:02:22','',0,'https://example.com/?post_type=entry&amp;p=342',71,'entry','',0);
